      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "Folks, this Leafs season's gone from Cup hopefuls to a flat-out <strong>disaster</strong>, wrapping up their home slate Monday with a wild 6-5 shootout loss to Dallas that screamed sloppy everywhere you looked. Sitting at 32-35-14, they're buried outside the playoff picture in the Atlantic&mdash;another lost year after Mitch Marner ditched town, leaving Auston Matthews and John Tavares carrying too much weight amid defensive meltdowns. Tavares showed captain's grit with a goal in the finale, Nylander's been flashing speed, but injuries and inconsistency killed 'em; no word on Arch Tiamov's status after his Marlies demotion, though Dennis Hildeby got the recall for a last hurrah. On the prospect front, they inked forward Landon Sim to a two-year entry-level deal&mdash;small spark for the rebuild. <strong>They wrap the regular season tonight in their finale</strong>, then it's offseason soul-searching for Craig Berube's crew.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
