      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "Folks, the Raptors are <strong>locked in as the No. 5 seed in the East</strong>, staring down a gritty first-round playoff clash with the No. 4 Cavaliers&mdash;proof they've clawed their way into the dance despite a rollercoaster regular season that landed them around .500 with a couple late stumbles snapping any real streak. Over the last few days, the big buzz was the NBA dropping <strong>the full Round 1 schedule</strong>, setting up a tense road start in Cleveland on Saturday[1]. Garrett Temple's been preaching steady defense&mdash;\"not letting shot-making affect us\"&mdash;and it's resonating, especially with Scottie Barnes heating up as the engine while Immanuel Quickley's nursing a minor ankle tweak but expected back soon&mdash;no major injuries derailing this squad. They've got the pieces: young fire from Gradey Dick off the bench, RJ Barrett's toughness inside. Don't sleep on Toronto upsetting the Cavs; they've got home games at Scotiabank Arena by week's end if they steal one early. <strong>Game 1's Saturday at 1 p.m. in Cleveland&mdash;puck drops on playoff chaos</strong>, so grab your coffee and tune in.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
